<TD align="left"><pre>





<strong><u>Which to use when:</u></strong>

1.A variable is declared as static if one wants the value of the variable to be persists between different 
  function calls.
2.A variable is declared as register storage class if those variables are used very often in program.
3.A variable is declared as external, when that variable is being used by almost all functions in the
  program.
4.Except all above conditions, we can declare variables as automatic. However default variable declaration 
  of variable as auto.



